<subSubSection id="C351654D405D293B13FDFDEFF69FFCDA" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF436C6405D293B13FDFDEFF69FFCDA" blockId="17.[151,1436,577,964]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="B93FEAD4405D293B13FDFDEFF32FFD8E" bold="true" box="[151,267,577,603]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the smallest of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D45405D293B115DFDECF096FD8E" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[567,690,578,603]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93FEAD4405D293B115DFDECF096FD8E" box="[567,690,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with body lengths of about 
<quantity id="4CB39B23405D293B1729FDEFF6B6FD89" box="[1091,1170,577,604]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
and a wing span of less than 
<quantity id="4CB39B23405D293B13BAFDCBF307FD55" box="[208,291,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 mm</quantity>
. The generic characters will distinguish it from other known 
<collectingCountry id="F35C7656405D293B10B3FDCBF660FDAA" box="[985,1092,613,639]" name="Suriname" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Suriname</collectingCountry>
cicadas but additional species of the genus will probably be found in the future. The species has a green head and thorax marked with piceous, a piceous abdomen, the postclypeus does not extend anteriorly beyond the supra-antennal plates when viewed from the dorsal side, and the fore wing radial and radiomedial crossveins lack infuscation. These characteristics can be used to distinguish it from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D45405D293B116FFD58F0A4FCDA" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[517,640,758,783]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93FEAD4405D293B116FFD58F0A4FCDA" box="[517,640,758,783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that may be found in 
<collectingCountry id="F35C7656405D293B10A4FD5BF61DFCDA" box="[974,1081,757,783]" name="Suriname" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Suriname</collectingCountry>
eventually.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C351654D405D293B13ADFCB7F6C0FCAE" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF436C6405D293B13ADFCB7F6C0FCAE" blockId="17.[151,1436,577,964]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="B93FEAD4405D293B13ADFCB7F345FCE6" bold="true" box="[199,353,793,819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Distribution.</emphasis>
